text.tspan: Other programs can hook into the addressbook by providing an icon, their name,
and what information to hook into, e.g. e-mail addresses or twitter accounts. When
clicking on such an action, the appropriate program will be launched with the specific
primary contact detail. If multiple contacts are selected, the action will be executed on
all selected contacts, e.g. mass e-mail.

In some cases, you want to set the type
of a detail, e.g. if it is a work phone or a
mobile phone. There are predefined types
but the user can also input arbitrary text.
Some entries can't be edited, as it is
remote data, e.g. an added Jabber address.
All possible entry types are listed,
and can be added with the "+" button
and removed with the "-" button. If
there is no data to display, the entry
type is still listed with the two buttons.
